{"body": "I really like this, but I don't think it's ready yet.\r\n\r\n* Those `?` methods, you can easily make them as alias method. That would be better because I believe it'll be done in C.\r\n* `is_` convention, doesn't make sense to have it.\r\n* It would be better if you're detecting which command we need, instead of throwing error that \"git/svn etc. is missing\"\r\n\r\nDo you mind make another patch and rebase your patch? I think that would be nice for 3.2.x", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1377029", "created_at": "2011-06-15T21:36:48Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/208#issuecomment-1377029", "updated_at": "2011-06-15T21:36:48Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 208, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/sikachu", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/f1c4a3bb1606cc4a61711e61e2fe6146?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F4a4526b1ec301744aba9526d78fcb2a6.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/received_events", "gravatar_id": "f1c4a3bb1606cc4a61711e61e2fe6146", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "sikachu", "type": "User", "id": 4912, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/sikachu/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523865b1bd3543c151012720"}, "id": 1377029, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/208"}
